Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.71,0:00:31.39,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so I thought this morning, if we had any time left over, if you can shut the
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.39,0:00:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,docket up for a chance, we could ask questions spontaneously, although we do them later.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.72,0:00:42.99,Default,,0,0,0,,It's usually more personal things later after we sign books and all.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.99,0:00:50.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought, because I want to make sure everyone gets it, if anybody has any questions or anything
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.28,0:00:53.49,Default,,0,0,0,,you'd like amplified or clarified, we'll do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.49,0:00:55.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got a few remaining minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.90,0:01:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So yes, oh, yeah, in a way that was going to come up next time when we talk about truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.00,0:01:22.45,Default,,0,0,0,,But I want you to also see that real is what you define as the qualifying, the qualification
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.45,0:01:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,of real.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.48,0:01:28.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Is real what is scientifically provable?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.28,0:01:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Is real what's experiential?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.17,0:01:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So real in a way is a way of approaching the subject, the defining the overall context
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.20,0:01:39.06,Default,,0,0,0,,by which we call it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.06,0:01:40.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Real.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.15,0:01:45.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there a reality that exists independent of human observation?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.31,0:01:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Quantum mechanics says no.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.06,0:01:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole universe is merely a consequence of observation.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.73,0:01:58.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether it's real really infers whether it exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.28,0:01:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.68,0:02:03.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And then how you define what exists is where the error comes in.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.70,0:02:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,To say that I have a foot is a subjective conclusion, actually.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.12,0:02:09.37,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't prove you have a foot.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.37,0:02:11.62,Default,,0,0,0,,But you experience it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.62,0:02:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So there is an experiential reality independent of what somebody might say about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.24,0:02:19.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So somebody might say that's not really a foot.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.65,0:02:20.65,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a hoof.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.65,0:02:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,In their language it's a hoof.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.12,0:02:25.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a hoof of a foot.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.12,0:02:30.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So anything that I . . . Is it really a . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.43,0:02:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,At a certain level it's all an illusion, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.36,0:02:45.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, because you're interpreting reality as what exists as form.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.71,0:02:49.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're talking about physical reality, physical existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.90,0:02:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact that you physically exist is a statement of truth because you can then verify that
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.84,0:02:56.87,Default,,0,0,0,,experientially.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.87,0:02:59.80,Default,,0,0,0,,What that means, however, is something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.80,0:03:01.53,Default,,0,0,0,,That's more abstract.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.53,0:03:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,How you define that reality?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.80,0:03:08.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The reality itself is independent of definition or how you look at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.59,0:03:11.21,Default,,0,0,0,,How you see the stare.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.21,0:03:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The stare is independent of how you perceive it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.19,0:03:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,But . . . . So then you call it . . . You think, well, eyes go through shape.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.03,0:03:16.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.12,0:03:16.18,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.18,0:03:21.41,Default,,0,0,0,,can make a statement about the stare and now you're talking about perception and now you're
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.41,0:03:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,talking about truth. So reality, what is real we're defining this morning as linear and confirmable
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.59,0:03:38.36,Default,,0,0,0,,through the senses. That it is here and it is here now and it is here at a certain time. We can
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.36,0:03:45.58,Default,,0,0,0,,confirm that. Then there are subjective realities that other people cannot confirm. That you had a
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.58,0:03:53.46,Default,,0,0,0,,dream about your dog last night and he was running after a rabbit. Now that is a fact. But a fact is
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.46,0:03:58.12,Default,,0,0,0,,something that is different than what is real. Somebody else could say well a dream is not real.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.43,0:04:06.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It may not be real to them. But it's still a fact that you had a dream last night and the content of
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.68,0:04:14.09,Default,,0,0,0,,that dream. So you end up again with subjectivity, first person reporting. And of course the validity
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.09,0:04:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,of first person reporting is the whole
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.02,0:04:16.44,Default,,0,0,0,,the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.44,0:04:16.47,Default,,0,0,0,,the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.47,0:04:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,, the battleground of scientific argument. You know whether personal testimony has any scientific
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.23,0:04:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,value. Of course it does because they do the very thing with their own scientific proof that the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.00,0:04:40.58,Default,,0,0,0,,subjective is irrational. And they state that as a fact. That's a subjective conclusion. They upend
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.58,0:04:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,their own argument about pedestrian scientism.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.11,0:04:45.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Just one last piece.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.24,0:04:45.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.74,0:04:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It's still a subjectivity.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.50,0:04:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.02,0:05:00.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Because what is it that says it's real? Consciousness actually.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.23,0:05:09.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all subjective and it's all within consciousness. That's why you know consciousness has no center. It has no beginning and no end.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.62,0:05:16.29,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why with consciousness calibration you can find out anything about anything anywhere in time or place.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.29,0:05:26.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not limited. It's beyond all limitation. So the truth and the truth the essence is beyond limitation. Facts and data.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.29,0:05:35.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And what's real are within the linear domain. Linear domain. So it's a less sophisticated domain.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.82,0:05:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.42,0:05:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.64,0:05:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on up a little closer so I can hear you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.00,0:06:00.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. There's a thing above and below to level 200. Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.17,0:06:05.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. About the contextual shift that happens to the value and the meaning of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.66,0:06:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.16,0:06:15.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm experiencing what used to be lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.06,0:06:16.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.13,0:06:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Things that I hear and see. And I'm wondering...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.04,0:06:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Well you would certainly agree with...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.86,0:06:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,change its importance its meaning the fact may be the same but how you how you hold it what it
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.12,0:06:36.77,Default,,0,0,0,,means to you is significant of course spiritually aligned people are almost always unconsciously
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.77,0:06:42.50,Default,,0,0,0,,using how does this serve my spiritual intention that's why it's good to make a declaration if
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.50,0:06:47.93,Default,,0,0,0,,you've never sat down formally made a declaration to the god i make a declaration of the purpose of
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.93,0:06:54.68,Default,,0,0,0,,my life i and glory and excelsis adio is a declaration uh glory to god in the most high
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.68,0:07:01.08,Default,,0,0,0,,that realigns everything that you experience in your life it either serves that end or it
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.08,0:07:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't serve that end so it's very powerful to make a declaration because it just does
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.44,0:07:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,change the whole context and significance and meaning and word there so i'm thinking about
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.50,0:07:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,in this world now the meaning of the setting that's what we have confirmed over and over
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.35,0:07:37.31,Default,,0,0,0,,that this is uh really
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.31,0:07:37.45,Default,,0,0,0,,you
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.48,0:07:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and uh because here you get to suffer out bad karma and make a choice
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.63,0:07:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,a more positive option you get to transcend and evolve now in other realms you don't have any
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.12,0:07:56.12,Default,,0,0,0,,choice hell is hell i tell you i've been in hell there was no option for anything positive
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.12,0:08:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,although well there was there was still the freedom of the will because i asked if there
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.83,0:08:07.58,Default,,0,0,0,,was a god i asked him to help me and if i was if it was only total hell there i wouldn't have
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.58,0:08:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,been able to have that thought
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.88,0:08:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,i think there are people to whom that thought never never does occur in hell and they're
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.19,0:08:21.37,Default,,0,0,0,,there permanently and the thought never does come to him oh god uh please forgive me i
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.37,0:08:29.41,Default,,0,0,0,,i ask for our salvation in the name of the lord so from the very bottom suddenly to shoot
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.41,0:08:36.36,Default,,0,0,0,,out all the way to the top like it was breathtaking you know if you would you know people i feel
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.36,0:08:43.55,Default,,0,0,0,,sorry people don't understand that hell is an experience of reality and it's far worse
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.55,0:08:48.27,Default,,0,0,0,,anybody could ever imagine. I don't want anybody here going there at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.79,0:08:51.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, ma'am?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.00,0:08:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You made the comment that consciousness calibration had dropped
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.92,0:09:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,from 207 to, say, 209. The consciousness level of mankind
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.88,0:09:07.13,Default,,0,0,0,,overall, overall, has dropped from 207 to 204.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.34,0:09:09.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And that was very recent. That was very recent, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.24,0:09:15.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Why calibrating it, how do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.87,0:09:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Well, you see
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.94,0:09:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,international war, you see the threat of nuclear.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.37,0:09:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You see primarily the same thing that the Pope pointed out,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.12,0:09:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and we've confirmed that in previous lectures. The Pope said
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.94,0:09:43.05,Default,,0,0,0,,the decline of Western civilization, and what may
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.05,0:09:46.01,Default,,0,0,0,,bring it to an end, is the decline of two things, you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.29,0:09:51.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Relativism and Islam. You put the two together and you've got destruction
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.13,0:09:52.13,Default,,0,0,0,,in the world as you know it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.25,0:10:00.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You have the opening the door for the wolf,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.85,0:10:04.05,Default,,0,0,0,,which is what do you call the road's
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.05,0:10:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,wooden pony, what do you call it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.72,0:10:11.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The Trojan horse, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.53,0:10:15.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The relativism is the Trojan horse.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.12,0:10:23.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And messianic Islam, then, is what's inside
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.24,0:10:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the horse. The imam, it will kill all of the Western world
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.88,0:10:32.59,Default,,0,0,0,,that will bring forth the 13th imam. It will save mankind, you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.55,0:10:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.39,0:10:46.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, the Pope said the decline of Western civilization, in fact,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.46,0:10:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,is even threatened by two things simultaneously.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.05,0:10:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Relativism, which decreases man's capacity to discern truth in the first place,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.05,0:10:58.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and that Islam, because of its fascist
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.67,0:11:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,totalitarian nature, you know, wants to kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.51,0:11:04.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.00,0:11:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,the combination of the two is enough to bring down Western civilization.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.48,0:11:16.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's, I think it's probably likely so, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.64,0:11:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, war is war. And when you get to nuclear war,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.38,0:11:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,you see, the nuclear threat is due to falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.08,0:11:31.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You understand, Iran and the whole nuclear threat was due to
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.05,0:11:37.15,Default,,0,0,0,,a couple of nuclear scientists who were compartmentalized personalities.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.46,0:11:43.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I won't even re-mention their names, but
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.61,0:11:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Klaus Fuchs and
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.52,0:11:50.28,Default,,0,0,0,,various people like that. America was an integrous nation and they had it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.22,0:11:57.34,Default,,0,0,0,,These people then, out of their narcissistic egotism, gave it to Russia who then sold it
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.34,0:12:02.05,Default,,0,0,0,,to everybody else. And the reason we all live in fear of nuclear annihilation now,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.86,0:12:09.41,Default,,0,0,0,,it was to the desecration of truth and integrity by a couple of compartmentalized personalities.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.41,0:12:15.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Whitaker Chambers was one, the whole answer about Whitaker Chambers, Klaus Fuchs, Robert Hanson,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.45,0:12:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and there's more and others, including some the world doesn't know about yet, because we can't
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.12,0:12:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,share everything we know with the world. But there are compartmentalized personalities out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.90,0:12:35.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Some are aware of the other personality and some are not. Generally they are not. Generally this
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.13,0:12:43.03,Default,,0,0,0,,person is completely segmented from this person, generally. But Klaus Fuchs and Robert Hanson and
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.03,0:12:47.58,Default,,0,0,0,,people like that, you know, now they've destroyed hundreds of CIA agents that were
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.70,0:12:48.77,Default,,0,0,0,,away.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.77,0:12:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Working to try and working for the CIA and the FBI, etc. But they are the ones that are responsible
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.52,0:13:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,for Iran's having a nuclear threat. And he now says that he intends to destroy all of western
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.96,0:13:10.87,Default,,0,0,0,,mankind. And when we check the arm, whether he means this, we always get yes, he means it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.53,0:13:21.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh dear, he means it, yeah. I'll kill you if I can. So the point you could do that is make sure he can.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.50,0:13:29.14,Default,,0,0,0,,But it was the violation of truth and integrity that brought this world to its present state.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.14,0:13:35.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So though the Pope's talking about now, the severity of the negativity of now is due to
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.46,0:13:40.89,Default,,0,0,0,,lack of integrity prior to that. It was World War II. It was the Manhattan Project and various
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.86,0:13:49.77,Default,,0,0,0,,people, the four from Oxford Four, etc. So that small group that set themselves above
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.51,0:13:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,is why we all live in jeopardy now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.51,0:13:59.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. So the interesting truth and false, as you can see, is more than just a spiritual
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.70,0:14:05.53,Default,,0,0,0,,sophistication. It has a very severe applications in mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.29,0:14:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So anyway, we got the Pope is right. I've agreed with him. You know, I was young,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.13,0:14:16.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I was very anti-Catholic. I have great hopes for the Pope.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.91,0:14:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I held a grudge against the Catholic Church for the Inquisition. That was it. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.63,0:14:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.36,0:14:39.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know if I can hear her. Honey, you'll have to come up or speak louder.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.22,0:14:45.98,Default,,0,0,0,,With the EM transmissions from the sun and how the earth is responding to 0.12 and the
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.98,0:14:50.37,Default,,0,0,0,,evolution of that, do you not think that that and what the physical
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.10,0:14:54.05,Default,,0,0,0,,ramifications of the earth responding to that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.05,0:14:58.94,Default,,0,0,0,,No. Yeah. No, the earth, see what man puts out is pollution.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.45,0:15:07.38,Default,,0,0,0,,What happens is they confuse pollution, which is one thing, with environmental warming, which is,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.38,0:15:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,another thing. So environmental warning is not due to pollution. We've gotten that over and over
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.15,0:15:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,again. It's environmental warming, a cyclic phases of the sun. And if you do ice core drillings down
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.75,0:15:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,10,000 years, you can see the, and that's now in the daily, it's now in the news. You know, it was,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.15,0:15:34.50,Default,,0,0,0,,it got people upset when we first used to say that. So environmental pollution is a different source.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.14,0:15:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So you got two different problems. One is pollution,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.19,0:15:44.35,Default,,0,0,0,,the other is environmental warming. This is not due to that. See, this is, it's not causality.
